"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:1.10.3\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">1.10.3</span> 標題：權杖（scepter）</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">經文出處</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： חקק</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： mchoqeq)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen49:10\">GEN 49:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num21:18\">NUM 21:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps60:9\">PSA 60:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps108:9\">PSA 108:9</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： מַטֶּה</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： mateh)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps110:2\">PSA 110:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer48:17\">JER 48:17</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： מַקֵּל</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： maqel)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer48:17\">JER 48:17</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： שֵׁבֶט</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： shevet)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen49:10\">GEN 49:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num24:17\">NUM 24:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg5:14\">JDG 5:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps45:7\">PSA 45:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps45:7\">PSA 45:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps125:3\">PSA 125:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa14:5\">ISA 14:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek19:11\">EZK 19:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek19:14\">EZK 19:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos1:5\">AMO 1:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos1:8\">AMO 1:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech10:11\">ZEC 10:11</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： שַׁרְבִיט</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： sharvit)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth4:11\">EST 4:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth5:2\">EST 5:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth5:2\">EST 5:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth8:4\">EST 8:4</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希： ῥάβδος</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： rhabdos)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:8\">HEB 1:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:8\">HEB 1:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/EsthGr5:2\">ESG 5:2</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希： σκῆπτρον</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： skēptron)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/EsthGr4:17\">ESG 4:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Wis6:21\">WIS 6:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Wis7:8\">WIS 7:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Wis10:14\">WIS 10:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir35:21\">SIR 35:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/EpJer1:12\">LJE 1:12</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">描述和用途</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/WEB-0364_scepter.jpg\" alt=\"權杖的頭\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">權杖的頭 (Gary Todd, Israel Museum, CC0, via Wikimedia Commons)</figcaption></figure>權杖是一根帶有裝飾的杖，通常至少有一部分是由貴金屬製成，象徵著統治者的權柄。統治者在行使某些職權時，會手握權杖。另參<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">1.2.4 竿、木棍、牧羊杖 (rod, club, shepherd’s staff)&lt;REALIA:1.2.4&gt;</a> 。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">翻譯</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>如果目標語言是用與首領相關的某個物品（如手杖、凳子或權杖）作為象徵，那麼在譯文中就可以使用這種象徵；例如，<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps45:7\">PSA 45:7</a> （《和》45:6）可以譯為，「你的儀杖表明你公正地統治你的百姓。」</p>\n<p>在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer48:17\">JER 48:17</a> 中，希伯來文<em>mateh</em> 和<em>maqel</em> 是平行關係。然而，翻譯者並不一定要用兩個相似的詞語來再現這種平行關係；例如，這節經文的後半部分可譯成，「那大能的杖和榮耀的棍竟然折斷了」（<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 直譯）；或「它強大的統治已被打破；它的榮耀和力量已不復存在」（<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 直譯）。這節經文是個比喻，所以這裡的重點不是權杖這個實物，而是在權柄。</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
